---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Bold from "../components/Bold.astro";
---

<div class="space-y-4">
    <p>
        <Bold>I don’t own a car</Bold>. I walk, cycle, and use Kingston Transit
        to get where I need to go.
    </p>

    <p>
        I walk to work, often cycle to get downtown, and take Kingston Transit
        to visit my parents and grandparents in Kingston’s west end.
    </p>

    <p>
        My life revolves around <Bold>active transportation</Bold> modes. Their ease
        is one of the things I love about living in Sydenham District, and why I choose
        to live here. Allocating budget funding to active transportation projects
        is a <Bold>priority</Bold> for me.
    </p>

    <p>
        Our active transportation options in Sydenham District are <Bold
            >the best in the City</Bold
        >, but I want to do a few things to make them <Bold>even better</Bold> for
        us:
    </p>

    <div class="flow-root">
        <!--
            Desktop image:
            It must appear before the list so every numbered section can wrap around it.
        -->
        <figure
            class="hidden md:float-right md:mb-5 md:ml-8 md:block md:w-72 lg:w-96"
        >
            <img
                src="/King St. (South)1.webp"
                alt="A section of sidewalk in Sydenham District"
                class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg"
                loading="lazy"
            />

            <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
                A worn-down path on the south side of King St.
            </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-4 pl-8 md:pl-10">
            <li>
                <Bold>Sidewalk Improvements:</Bold> I will advocate for building missing
                sections of <Bold>sidewalks</Bold>/<Bold>multi-use paths</Bold> in
                the following areas in our district:

                <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
                    <li>
                        <Bold>King St.</Bold> (south side) between <Bold
                            >Sir John A. Macdonald Blvd.</Bold
                        > and <Bold>Breakwater Park</Bold>.
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <Bold>Court St.</Bold>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        Both sides of <Bold>Sir John A. Macdonald Blvd.</Bold>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <!-- Mobile image: appears after the Sidewalk Improvements section -->
                <figure class="mt-5 md:hidden">
                    <img
                        src="/King St. (South)1.webp"
                        alt="A section of sidewalk in Sydenham District"
                        class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg"
                        loading="lazy"
                    />

                    <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
                        Proposed sidewalk improvement area.
                    </figcaption>
                </figure>
            </li>

            <li>
                <Bold>Pedestrian Crossing Lights:</Bold>

                <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
                    <li>
                        <Bold>Add</Bold> a pedestrian crossing light on <Bold
                            >Union St.</Bold
                        > at <Bold>MacDonnell St.</Bold> to <Bold
                            >improve safety</Bold
                        > at this <Bold>existing crossing guard location</Bold> for
                        Winston Churchill Public School students and improve safety
                        for everyone crossing at this location at any time of day.
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <Bold>Add</Bold> a pedestrian crossing light on <Bold
                            >Johnson St.</Bold
                        > at <Bold>College St.</Bold> to provide a safe place for
                        pedestrians to cross in the section of Johnson St. between
                        <Bold>Palace Rd.</Bold> and <Bold>Macdonnell St.</Bold>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li>
                <Bold>Transit Frequency:</Bold>
                <Bold>Increase the frequency</Bold> of Kingston Transit service routes
                along <Bold>Union St.</Bold> and <Bold>King St.</Bold> that connect
                Sydenham District to <Bold>downtown</Bold> and the rest of the City,
                including commercial areas such as the Kingston Centre and the Cataraqui
                Mall.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-cool-orange">
        <u><Bold>You should vote for me if:</Bold></u>
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-8 md:pl-10">
        <li>
            You love to <Bold>walk</Bold>, <Bold>cycle</Bold>, or <Bold
                >take transit</Bold
            > (or want to be able to do these things more often!).
        </li>
        <li>
            You want to see some really <Bold>simple but meaningful</Bold> changes
            where we have <Bold>missing sidewalks</Bold> and can <Bold
                >add pedestrian crossing lights</Bold
            >.
        </li>
        <li>
            You see active transportation as a budget <Bold>priority</Bold> for our
            district, especially with the growth in student population expected in
            the upcoming years.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-cool-orange">
        <u
            ><Bold
                >If you’re not sure if you should vote for me, here is what you
                should ask the other candidates:</Bold
            ></u
        >
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-8 md:pl-10">
        <li>
            How often do you <Bold>walk</Bold>, <Bold>cycle</Bold>, or <Bold
                >take transit</Bold
            > to go places in our District? When was the last time you took a trip
            on Kingston Transit?
        </li>
        <li>
            Is <Bold>active transportation</Bold> a priority for you when it comes
            to setting the budget?
        </li>
        <li>
            Will you commit to getting <Bold>missing sidewalks</Bold> completed and
            more pedestrian lights installed?
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
